<Author>enigmajic
<Content>Great place (especially for the money) A lot of nice things have been said about this hotel, so I'm not going to repeat too much of it. While in the outer skirts of Barcelona proper, it is still metro-accessible and has a wonderful view of the city towards the mountains. And I later found out during the three days I was there that it was also very close to the Sant Andreas (sp?) train station where you can take a train to the airport. Nice sized rooms with double bed, but the mattress was on the harder side. The rooms are clean but the amenities are on the sparse side. Though I do appreciate the inclusion of soap dispensers for the sink and the shower - saves my supply for other later hotels I'll need them in. Bar opened 24hrs and the staff was friendly and helpful. I highly recommend this hotel and any other of the Accor line for any of your vacation needs. 
