<Content>fantastic Hiya, myself  Fella read some bad reviews on the Ibis at heron city and I must say we were a little worried !! All i can say is i'm so so happy we didnt cancel, Yes the hotel is very slightly out of the centre, (ten mins on the metro ride) however its a leisurly ten minute walk to the nearest Metro station, down a wide tree lined avenue, just to stop and watch the old men playing small silver ball bowling is a sight in itself. The hotel is spotless, the reception staff a fab bunch of people, and the bar staff were amazing, even giving me free liquers to choose, they were all kind and very helpfull. We ate in Frankie  Bennys, Pizza Marzano and Asador (steak bar) all were fab, if you tell them you are staying at the Ibis you will get 10% discount. All the air conditioning worked, and the rooms were cleaned every day to a high standard. DO NOT be put off by some of the bad reviews it was FANTASTIC, we will certainly be going again. Enjoy. Love Caroline  Ian (Bradford, West Yorkshire, UK) 
