<Author>DCGlasgow
<Content>Value hotel with three REAL issues My review is based upon these real issues:We stayed in the Meridiana Ibis from 2/3/07 - 5/3/07 (a weekend). BEAR this in Mind. The air conditioning is not switched on until May and our south facing room was stuffy and uncomfortable (28 degrees according to my travel thermometer. Barcelona was enjoying temperatures in the 20+). The windows have no handles so opening them is a REAL issue.I had to go to the Night Porter at reception to ask for the air con to be switched on to which he refused. His solution was to give me a handle for the window! (bizarre). On opening the quadruple glazed windows the noise of the music from the adjacent night club was unbearable (this went on until 6a.m. hence the super dooper glazing)We took issue with the manager the next morning who stated that the air con is indeed off until May. Her solution was to suggest switching it on during the day when other residents were out so the room would be cooler.Indeed she hinted that the residents may find it cold at night if air con remained on. I asked why not just leave on as individual rooms could turn up their air con to heat the room. she just shrugged her shoulders (maybe cost cutting???). The compromise was to move rooms to the rear of the hotel were it was cooler (north facing) but indeed on opening this room's windows the noise from the near by Heron City air conditioning units (contrary to the Hotel's being off!) was also loud. However the room was cooler so felt better with windows shut .On a positive note the hotel is value for money. it is situated in a nice part of town (the south facing views from hotel are lovely) with a pleasant walk along the avenue Meridiana to the Fabra I Puig metro (buy a T10 ticket for value for money = 10 trips for around 6.80 euros you can buy at the ticket vending machines on entry to the metro).For the weary traveler who can't face going back into town after being out all day, Heron City will offer some comfort in restaurants and cafe's. Try the Argentinian restaurant for something different- staff very helpful if needing translation of Menu's. Also all restaurants within Heron City offer 10% discount on bills if staying at this Ibis- the Hotel forgot to tell us this.We wouldn't stay here again not solely because of the issues with air con/ windows but also because in getting to know the city you notice more intimate/ with character accommodation. If staying from May- October when the air con is on you shouldn't encounter the problems we had. 
<Date>Mar 6, 2007
