<Author>totfl
<Content>great, low price hotel. Ideal for football travellers My partner and I stayed at the Ibis Meridiana on March 31-April 3rd 2006. A very clean, well maintained hotel, that for the price I can't praise highly enough. A 5-10 min walk from the Fabra I Puig metro station, along a tree lined boulevard where senors play boules, or you can stop and watch a football match on the local pitch, The metro station is about 5 mins from Brcelona Nord bus terminal and 10 mins from Placa Catalunya. Heron City is behind the hotel with a cinema and a plethora of American style diners. (the best Frankie and Benny's I've been in). The only problem with the hotel is getting back to it late at night/early morning for party animals, the taxi queues in Barca are some of the worst I've ever seen. I'd recommend this hotel to people going over to Barca for the weekend. We took in el Clasico (Barca v Madrid) when we were over. Superb. 
