<Content>Ibis Meridiana - great value! We visited Barcelona in late October, 2004. While not in the heart of the city, we thought the location, for the price could not be beat. We paid 76 euros per night for a nice sized room that was very modern and up to date in a clean comfortable hotel. It was about a 10 minute walk to the metro station that took us to Placa Catalunya in 15 minutes or so.The Ibis offers a cold breakfast buffett for 6 euros that was not a bad deal. Since we're Americans, we felt rather comforted by the familiar looking environs of the Heron City entertainment complex next door. We really enjoyed our stay in Barcelona. It is a fantastic city with days worth of stuff to see and do. I'd highly recommend the Ibis Meridiana! 
