<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Beautiful Although slightly out of Barcelonas centre, this hotel is great value and maybe you get a slightly different perspective on Barcelonian life than you would if you just stayed in an overpriced hotel in the city centre? Each morning and night you can have a leisurely walk from the hotel to the nearest tube station along an avenue with boules areas, football pitches and park area and may catch a glimse of local life, with blocks of flats near by. The views from the hotel are also plesant. At night, looking up at the hotel, the top lights up in a multitude of colours which is great fun.The hotel itself is clean and tidy, with generally helpful staff. The rooms are air conditioned (which is a relief from the near 40 C temperatures we had when we stayed) with double beds, a shower room, tv with a wide selection of different language stations and blackout curtains. The hotel is located within Heron City, an entertainment complex with cinema, restaurants and bowling which can provide a plesant night out on your doorstep. Highly recommended for a stay in one of the worlds greatest cities. 
