<Author>Becks_Edin
<Content>Excellent bargain Having been saved from a 'bargain' cesspit by the reviews on this site, felt it my duty to report. Although the Ibis Meridiana is of course a chain hotel with no discernible character and is not in the main city centre, it is so cheap compared to the amazingly high prices generally in Barcelona, it was my final choice. The room was just fine: clean, spacious, stylish, no worries. Very very helpful  friendly staff too. The only thing that had put me off slightly (such a snob) is that it's situated in Heron City, an American style complex of bowling alley, Macdonalds etc. Maybe it was just the time of year (April) but actually it was rather nice - it's small and seemed to be only populated by locals having a coffee and letting their kids play on the automated fountains -you stand on buttons and make the water spray, it's got lights at night too!Not a particularly attractive part of Barcelona but you don't go for the hotel room, right? A short walk to the metro station, passing 'Old Man's Alley' as my son called it (boules playing in the local park)and just 10 minutes on the superb metro right into Place Catalunya.At 49 euros for the room, it was the cheapest I could find (apart from aforementioned cesspit).Thorougly recommended. 
